Poor communication of information through digital media can lead to a number of misunderstandings. For instance, a student who sends an email to a professor without a subject, greeting, and other elements of courtesy can be perceived as impolite and unprofessional. This can lead to a situation where the student’s request is ignored or viewed negatively. 

This can be averted by observing simple email etiquette. In addition, it is advisable to scrutinize the message before sending it. This will ensure that a positive impression is created, and the message is taken seriously.
